text: Visualizing the architecture we learn, our approach is adaptive to different new coming tasks by reusing more modules while learning similar tasks and adding more modules while learning dissimilar tasks. (In this fig, task1 is similar to task3, task4 is similar to task5) https://t.co/9PeZrBVe1i

Together with pseudo experience replay proposed in LAMOL, our approach achieves the most robust performance in both similar task sequences and dissimilar task sequences with few parameters. https://t.co/OOt1WtkPek

In this work, we propose continual sequence generation with adaptive composition modules: Before training on a new task, we use a decision stage to decide the composition of modules for the new task (either add or reuse an adapter module in each transformer layer). https://t.co/tbfIBeVcjv

Current approaches for continual NLP either always reuse existing parameters to learn new tasks or blindly add new parameters for every new task, while the former is vulnerable to severe forgetting and the latter prevents knowledge transfer. https://t.co/Y14Cdu6fwl
